Cook: It is a shame that you mar the most beautiful post you ever wrote. It is a shame that you can not see the hatred you preach, instead of the nobility you say you believe in. <br>
Two examples:  (1) &quot;a war protester (same as resister, same as peace  demonstrator, same as coward, same as conscientious objector, same as etc…&quot;. That is an insult to ever non-soldier in our country. There is quite a difference between each catagory. It would be if I said Sarg, Leut. Colonel, General, what the hell, they are all the same. Or, marine, sailor, soldier, all the same. Or, U.S.Marine, U.S. Navy, U.S. Army, U.S. Air Force, all the same.  Your hatred makes you pull out that broad brush again.  When will you learn to get over your anger?   (2) &quot;communist gooks&quot;. Here we go again, dehumanize and then kill. What an ugly word &quot;gook&quot; is.  Only the person who uses it is uglier.  Welcome home Cook, can't wait to see the damage you do to the site that has changed since you left.<br><br>
Your closing memark is quite interesting, that you are now: <br>
&quot;Today we have begun to climb out of the rice paddies at home where we have been  pinned down all these years..&quot; finally says it all, and says it where you are at.  You really believe that the American Public has &quot;pinned you down&quot; for all these years?  Man, ain't no one that important.  The war ended for most of us long ago. Some day it will end for you. I hope you find peace along the way.<br><br>
